# The Dockerfile does `COPY . .`, so this file is the control that keeps secrets and
# junk out of the image. Image layers are readable by anyone who can pull the image.

# Secrets. Non-negotiable.
.env
.env.*

# VCS and agent/editor state
.git
.gitignore
.claude
CLAUDE.md
.attic/

# Python build and environment artifacts
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/

# Not needed at runtime
docs/
README.md

# Generated audit log: working scaffolding (see .gitignore), and it reached 555 KB during
# development. It must not bloat or leak into the image. The data CSV is runtime-required
# and is NOT excluded -- and neither is evals.py: the README's section (b) is built on that
# suite, so a reviewer who only runs Docker must still be able to run it:
#   docker compose run --rm web python evals.py
query_audit.jsonl
*.jsonl

# OS noise
.DS_Store
